{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861455058,"sessionID":"ses_28669b5caffeqYLfdG2bo5GERy","part":{"id":"prt_d79968e14001Cdu2bbkDCXOTKU","messageID":"msg_d7996580e001T8wS20KewMbYC6","sessionID":"ses_28669b5caffeqYLfdG2bo5GERy","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_64c10087a0dc4dc8b94764f9","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# Delta Spec ŌĆö AR-026: K8s/AgentCube Provider\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n\n## Scope\n\nThis delta spec adds GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios for the `KubernetesProvider` and `AgentCubeProvider` classes, provider selection logic in CLI commands, and K8s-specific error handling not covered by the base `cli-toolkit/spec.md`.\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: `KubernetesProvider._ensure_namespace`\nThe system SHALL create the target namespace if it does not already exist before deploying resources.\n\n#### Scenario: Namespace already exists\n- **GIVEN** `KubernetesProvider` is initialized with `namespace=\"default\"`\n- **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL detect the namespace exists and take no action\n\n#### Scenario: Namespace does not exist\n- **GIVEN** `KubernetesProvider` is initialized with `namespace=\"my-agents\"`\n- **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace` is called and the namespace is not found\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create the namespace via the K8s API and log the creation\n\n#### Scenario: Namespace creation failure\n- **GIVEN** the user lacks RBAC permissions to create namespaces\n- **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace` is called for a non-existent namespace\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise an exception with the K8s API error surfaced to the caller\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: `KubernetesProvider._create_deployment`\nThe system SHALL create or patch a Kubernetes `Deployment` with the agent container spec.\n\n#### Scenario: Create new deployment\n- **GIVEN** no existing deployment with the given name\n- **WHEN** `_create_deployment` is called with `name`, `image_url`, `port`, `replicas`, and optional `env_vars`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create a `Deployment` with:\n  - `metadata.name` = sanitized name\n  - `spec.replicas` = provided replicas (default 1)\n  - `spec.template.spec.containers[0].image` = `image_url`\n  - `spec.template.spec.containers[0].ports[0].containerPort` = `port`\n  - `spec.template.spec.containers[0].env` populated from `env_vars` if provided\n  - `spec.template.spec.containers[0].command` set from `entrypoint` if provided\n\n#### Scenario: Patch existing deployment\n- **GIVEN** a deployment with the given name already exists\n- **WHEN** `_create_deployment` is called with updated `image_url` or `replicas`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL patch the existing deployment with the new spec\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: `KubernetesProvider._create_service`\nThe system SHALL create or patch a `NodePort` `Service` to expose the deployment.\n\n#### Scenario: Create NodePort service with auto-assigned port\n- **GIVEN** `node_port` is `None`\n- **WHEN** `_create_service` is called with `name` and `port`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create a `Service` of type `NodePort` with K8s auto-assigned node port in range 30000-32767\n\n#### Scenario: Create NodePort service with explicit port\n- **GIVEN** `node_port` is provided (e.g., `30080`)\n- **WHEN** `_create_service` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create a `Service` with `spec.ports[0].nodePort` = the provided value\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid NodePort range\n- **GIVEN** `node_port` is outside 30000-32767\n- **WHEN** `_create_service` is called\n- **THEN** the K8s API SHALL reject the request and the system SHALL surface the error\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status`\nThe system SHALL retrieve the current status of a deployed agent including pod health.\n\n#### Scenario: Agent running with ready pods\n- **GIVEN** a deployment exists with all replicas ready\n- **WHEN** `get_agent_status` is called with `agent_name`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return a dict containing `status: \"running\"`, `replicas`, `ready_replicas`, and pod details\n\n#### Scenario: Agent deployment not found\n- **GIVEN** no deployment exists with the given name\n- **WHEN** `get_agent_status` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return `{\"status\": \"not_found\"}` or raise an appropriate exception\n\n#### Scenario: Agent in rollout progress\n- **GIVEN** a deployment exists but not all replicas are ready\n- **WHEN** `get_agent_status` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return status indicating rollout in progress with `ready_replicas < replicas`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: `KubernetesProvider._sanitize_name`\nThe system SHALL sanitize agent names to be valid Kubernetes resource names.\n\n#### Scenario: Valid name unchanged\n- **GIVEN** a name containing only lowercase alphanumeric characters and hyphens\n- **WHEN** `_sanitize_name` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return the name unchanged\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid characters replaced\n- **GIVEN** a name containing uppercase letters, underscores, or other invalid characters\n- **WHEN** `_sanitize_name` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return a name with invalid characters replaced (e.g., lowercased, underscores ŌåÆ hyphens)\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: `AgentCubeProvider._ensure_namespace`\nThe system SHALL ensure the target namespace exists before creating AgentRuntime CRs.\n\n#### Scenario: Namespace created for CR deployment\n- **GIVEN** `AgentCubeProvider` is initialized with a non-default namespace\n- **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace` is called and namespace does not exist\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create the namespace before proceeding with CR operations\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime`\nThe system SHALL create or patch an `AgentRuntime` custom resource with full spec.\n\n#### Scenario: Create AgentRuntime CR with all fields\n- **GIVEN** valid metadata with `router_url`, `workload_manager_url`, readiness probe config\n- **WHEN** `deploy_agent_runtime` is called with `agent_name`, `image_url`, `port`, `entrypoint`, `env_vars`, and probe settings\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create an `AgentRuntime` CR with:\n  - `spec.image` = `image_url`\n  - `spec.port` = `port`\n  - `spec.entrypoint` = `entrypoint` if provided\n  - `spec.env` = merged from `env_vars` + `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` + `ROUTER_URL` (from params or environment)\n  - `spec.readinessProbe` with `httpGet.path` and `httpGet.port` from probe settings\n  - `spec.sessionTimeout` = `\"15m\"`\n  - `spec.maxSessionDuration` = `\"8h\"`\n  - `spec.imagePullSecrets` = `[{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]`\n\n#### Scenario: Patch existing AgentRuntime CR\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` CR with the given name already exists\n- **WHEN** `deploy_agent_runtime` is called with updated fields\n- **THEN** the system SHALL patch the existing CR with the new spec\n\n#### Scenario: Missing readiness probe fields\n- **GIVEN** metadata lacks `readiness_probe_path` or `readiness_probe_port`\n- **WHEN** `deploy_agent_runtime` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL either use defaults or omit the readiness probe from the CR spec\n\n#### Scenario: Environment variable fallback\n- **GIVEN** `env_vars` does not contain `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` or `ROUTER_URL`\n- **WHEN** `deploy_agent_runtime` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL read `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` / `ROUTER_URL` from the process environment and inject them into the CR spec\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: `AgentCubeProvider._sanitize_name`\nThe system SHALL sanitize names for AgentRuntime CR resource naming.\n\n#### Scenario: CR name sanitization\n- **GIVEN** an agent name with invalid K8s characters\n- **WHEN** `_sanitize_name` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return a DNS-1123 compliant name suitable for CR `metadata.name`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: `AgentCubeProvider.get_agent_runtime`\nThe system SHALL retrieve an existing AgentRuntime CR by name and namespace.\n\n#### Scenario: CR exists\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` CR exists with the given name in the namespace\n- **WHEN** `get_agent_runtime` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return the CR object as a dict\n\n#### Scenario: CR not found\n- **GIVEN** no `AgentRuntime` CR exists with the given name\n- **WHEN** `get_agent_runtime` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return `None`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Provider selection in CLI commands\nThe system SHALL route publish/status/invoke operations to the correct provider based on the `--provider` flag.\n\n#### Scenario: Publish with `--provider agentcube`\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `publish --provider agentcube`\n- **WHEN** the publish command executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use `AgentCubeProvider` and call `deploy_agent_runtime`\n\n#### Scenario: Publish with `--provider k8s`\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `publish --provider k8s`\n- **WHEN** the publish command executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use `KubernetesProvider` and call `deploy_agent` with `replicas` from options\n\n#### Scenario: Status with `--provider agentcube`\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `status --provider agentcube`\n- **WHEN** the status command executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use `StatusRuntime` with `provider=\"agentcube\"` and call `_get_cr_k8s_status`\n\n#### Scenario: Status with `--provider k8s`\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `status --provider k8s`\n- **WHEN** the status command executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use `StatusRuntime` with `provider=\"k8s\"` and call `_get_k8s_status`\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke with `--provider agentcube`\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `invoke --provider agentcube`\n- **WHEN** the invoke command executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use `InvokeRuntime` with `provider=\"agentcube\"` and rewrite URL to AgentRuntime CR invocation path when `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke with `--provider k8s`\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `invoke --provider k8s`\n- **WHEN** the invoke command executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use `InvokeRuntime` with `provider=\"k8s\"` and invoke via standard deployment endpoint\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: K8s client initialization error handling\nThe system SHALL handle failures when initializing Kubernetes clients gracefully.\n\n#### Scenario: Kubeconfig not found\n- **GIVEN** no kubeconfig file exists at the default or specified path\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider` or `AgentCubeProvider` is initialized\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise an exception with a message indicating kubeconfig is missing\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid kubeconfig\n- **GIVEN** a kubeconfig file exists but contains invalid YAML or cluster config\n- **WHEN** the provider is initialized\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise an exception with the parsing or connection error\n\n#### Scenario: Cluster unreachable\n- **GIVEN** kubeconfig is valid but the cluster API server is unreachable\n- **WHEN** any provider method makes a K8s API call\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise a connection error surfaced via CLI `_handle_error`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: CRD availability check\nThe system SHALL verify that the AgentRuntime CRD is installed before attempting CR operations.\n\n#### Scenario: CRD not installed\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube` but the `agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` CRD is not registered\n- **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider` attempts to create or get a CR\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise an error indicating the CRD is not installed\n\n#### Scenario: CRD installed and accessible\n- **GIVEN** the CRD is registered and the user has RBAC permissions\n- **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider` performs CR operations\n- **THEN** the system SHALL succeed in creating/reading/updating AgentRuntime CRs\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775861455051,"end":1775861455056}}}}
