{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861462041,"sessionID":"ses_28669b5caffeqYLfdG2bo5GERy","part":{"id":"prt_d7997714d001AC8lp0eu3spL1K","messageID":"msg_d79976919001otqXA851gaV2SY","sessionID":"ses_28669b5caffeqYLfdG2bo5GERy","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_8ce3eb51b27f41eb8827438b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-023: CLI invoke/status ÕæĮõ╗ż ŌĆö Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `cmd/cli`\n6: - **Language:** Python\n7: - **Size:** M\n8: - **Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/spec.md`, `cli-toolkit/design.md`\n9: \n10: ## Scope\n11: \n12: This delta spec covers the `invoke` and `status` CLI commands, their runtime classes (`InvokeRuntime`, `StatusRuntime`), and associated provider integrations (`AgentCubeProvider`, `KubernetesProvider`).\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## invoke Command\n17: \n18: ### Requirement: invoke command entry point\n19: \n20: The system SHALL provide an `invoke` subcommand that POSTs JSON payload to the published agent endpoint, supporting both `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR) and `k8s` (Deployment/Service) providers.\n21: \n22: #### Scenario: invoke options and defaults\n23: \n24: - **GIVEN** the user runs `invoke`\n25: - **THEN** defaults SHALL be:\n26:   - `workspace` = `\".\"` (`-f` / `--workspace`, `str`)\n27:   - `payload` = `\"{}\"` (`--payload`, `str`)\n28:   - `header_list` = `None` (`--header`, repeatable `List[str]`)\n29:   - `provider` = `\"agentcube\"` (`--provider`, `str`)\n30:   - `verbose` = `False` (`--verbose`, `bool`)\n31: \n32: #### Scenario: payload JSON parsing\n33: \n34: - **GIVEN** the user provides `--payload '{\"input\": \"hello\"}'`\n35: - **WHEN** the command parses it\n36: - **THEN** the system SHALL deserialize it to `{\"input\": \"hello\"}` and pass it to `InvokeRuntime.invoke`\n37: \n38: #### Scenario: invalid payload JSON\n39: \n40: - **GIVEN** `--payload` is not valid JSON (e.g., `--payload '{bad}'`)\n41: - **WHEN** the command parses it\n42: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `Error: Invalid JSON payload: {detail}` in red and exit with code `1` (before calling `_handle_error`)\n43: \n44: #### Scenario: header parsing\n45: \n46: - **GIVEN** the user provides `--header \"Authorization: Bearer token123\"`\n47: - **WHEN** headers are parsed\n48: - **THEN** the system SHALL split on the first `:` to produce `{\"Authorization\": \"Bearer token123\"}` (stripped key/value)\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: invalid header format\n51: \n52: - **GIVEN** a header string without a `:` separator (e.g., `--header \"BadHeader\"`)\n53: - **WHEN** headers are parsed\n54: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `Error: Invalid header format. Expected 'key:value'.` in red and exit with code `1`\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: multiple headers\n57: \n58: - **GIVEN** the user provides `--header \"Authorization: Bearer token\" --header \"X-Custom: value\"`\n59: - **WHEN** headers are parsed\n60: - **THEN** the system SHALL merge all into a single `Dict[str, str]`\n61: \n62: #### Scenario: session header injection\n63: \n64: - **GIVEN** metadata contains `session_id`\n65: - **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` runs\n66: - **THEN** the HTTP request SHALL include header `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` with the session value\n67: \n68: #### Scenario: AgentCube provider URL rewriting\n69: \n70: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube` and `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`\n71: - **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime._invoke_agent_via_agentcube` runs\n72: - **THEN** the endpoint URL SHALL be rewritten to `{base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n73: \n74: #### Scenario: invoke prerequisites validation\n75: \n76: - **GIVEN** the workspace lacks published metadata (no `agent_id` or `agent_endpoint`)\n77: - **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime._validate_invoke_prerequisites` runs\n78: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating the agent must be published first\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: successful invoke response\n81: \n82: - **GIVEN** a valid endpoint and payload\n83: - **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime._direct_http_invocation` completes\n84: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print the response (Rich-formatted if JSON, raw text otherwise)\n85: \n86: #### Scenario: invoke HTTP error\n87: \n88: - **GIVEN** the endpoint returns a non-2xx status\n89: - **WHEN** `_direct_http_invocation` receives the response\n90: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise an exception surfaced via `_handle_error` with the status code and response body\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: invoke error handling\n93: \n94: - **GIVEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` raises\n95: - **WHEN** `verbose` is `True`\n96: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `Error invoking agent: {e}` in red, print a full traceback, and exit with code `1`\n97: \n98: ---\n99: \n100: ## status Command\n101: \n102: ### Requirement: status command entry point\n103: \n104: The system SHALL provide a `status` subcommand that loads workspace metadata and displays agent status in a Rich `Table`.\n105: \n106: #### Scenario: status options and defaults\n107: \n108: - **GIVEN** the user runs `status`\n109: - **THEN** defaults SHALL be:\n110:   - `workspace` = `\".\"` (`-f` / `--workspace`, `str`)\n111:   - `provider` = `\"agentcube\"` (`--provider`, `str`)\n112:   - `verbose` = `False` (`--verbose`, `bool`)\n113: \n114: #### Scenario: not published status\n115: \n116: - **GIVEN** metadata has no `agent_id`\n117: - **WHEN** `StatusRuntime.get_status` returns `status == \"not_published\"`\n118: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print guidance to run `publish` first and exit with code `1`\n119: \n120: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime CR status\n121: \n122: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube` and the CR exists in K8s\n123: - **WHEN** `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status` runs\n124: - **THEN** status SHALL be read from `cr_object[\"status\"]` when present (fields: `status`, `agentEndpoint`), else `created_no_status`, else `not_found_in_k8s`\n125: \n126: #### Scenario: standard K8s status\n127: \n128: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `k8s`\n129: - **WHEN** `StatusRuntime._get_k8s_status` runs\n130: - **THEN** the system SHALL query `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status` and return deployment/pod status\n131: \n132: #### Scenario: status display\n133: \n134: - **GIVEN** status data is available\n135: - **WHEN** the status command completes\n136: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL render a Rich `Table` with columns: Field, Value (including at minimum: Agent Name, Status, Endpoint, Version, Provider)\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: status error\n139: \n140: - **GIVEN** `StatusRuntime.get_status` returns `status == \"error\"`\n141: - **WHEN** the status command processes the result\n142: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print the error details and exit with code `1`\n143: \n144: #### Scenario: status error handling\n145: \n146: - **GIVEN** `StatusRuntime.get_status` raises\n147: - **WHEN** `verbose` is `True`\n148: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `Error getting status: {e}` in red, print a full traceback, and exit with code `1`\n149: \n150: ---\n151: \n152: ## InvokeRuntime\n153: \n154: ### Requirement: InvokeRuntime class\n155: \n156: The system SHALL implement `InvokeRuntime` with provider-aware invocation logic.\n157: \n158: #### Scenario: constructor\n159: \n160: - **GIVEN** `InvokeRuntime(verbose=False, provider=\"agentcube\")` is instantiated\n161: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n162: - **THEN** `self.verbose` and `self.provider` SHALL be set accordingly\n163: \n164: #### Scenario: invoke method\n165: \n166: - **GIVEN** a valid `workspace_path`, `payload` (Dict), and optional `headers` (Dict[str, str])\n167: - **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` is called\n168: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n169:   1. Call `_validate_invoke_prerequisites(workspace_path)` to get metadata, agent_id, and endpoint\n170:   2. If `provider == \"agentcube\"`, call `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube`\n171:   3. Otherwise, call `_direct_http_invocation`\n172:   4. Return the response\n173: \n174: #### Scenario: _validate_invoke_prerequisites\n175: \n176: - **GIVEN** a valid workspace with published metadata\n177: - **WHEN** `_validate_invoke_prerequisites` runs\n178: - **THEN** it SHALL return `(metadata, agent_id, endpoint)` tuple\n179: \n180: #### Scenario: _invoke_agent_via_agentcube\n181: \n182: - **GIVEN** an agent_id, payload, headers, endpoint, and workspace_path\n183: - **WHEN** `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube` runs\n184: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n185:   1. Rewrite endpoint if `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`\n186:   2. Add `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` header if `metadata.session_id` exists\n187:   3. POST JSON to the endpoint\n188:   4. Return the parsed response\n189: \n190: #### Scenario: _direct_http_invocation\n191: \n192: - **GIVEN** an endpoint, payload, headers, and workspace_path\n193: - **WHEN** `_direct_http_invocation` runs\n194: - **THEN** it SHALL POST JSON to `{endpoint}` and return the response dict\n195: \n196: ---\n197: \n198: ## StatusRuntime\n199: \n200: ### Requirement: StatusRuntime class\n201: \n202: The system SHALL implement `StatusRuntime` with provider-aware status retrieval.\n203: \n204: #### Scenario: constructor\n205: \n206: - **GIVEN** `StatusRuntime(verbose=False, provider=\"agentcube\")` is instantiated\n207: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n208: - **THEN** `self.verbose` and `self.provider` SHALL be set accordingly\n209: \n210: #### Scenario: get_status method\n211: \n212: - **GIVEN** a `workspace_path` and optional `provider`\n213: - **WHEN** `StatusRuntime.get_status` is called\n214: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n215:   1. Load metadata from workspace\n216:   2. If no `agent_id`, return `{\"status\": \"not_published\"}`\n217:   3. If `provider == \"agentcube\"`, call `_get_cr_k8s_status`\n218:   4. Otherwise, call `_get_k8s_status`\n219:   5. Return the status dict\n220: \n221: #### Scenario: _get_cr_k8s_status with existing CR\n222: \n223: - **GIVEN** the AgentRuntime CR exists and has a `status` field\n224: - **WHEN** `_get_cr_k8s_status` runs\n225: - **THEN** it SHALL return `{\"status\": cr_status, \"endpoint\": cr_agentEndpoint, ...}`\n226: \n227: #### Scenario: _get_cr_k8s_status with CR but no status\n228: \n229: - **GIVEN** the AgentRuntime CR exists but has no `status` field\n230: - **WHEN** `_get_cr_k8s_status` runs\n231: - **THEN** it SHALL return `{\"status\": \"created_no_status\"}`\n232: \n233: #### Scenario: _get_cr_k8s_status with missing CR\n234: \n235: - **GIVEN** the AgentRuntime CR does not exist\n236: - **WHEN** `_get_cr_k8s_status` runs\n237: - **THEN** it SHALL return `{\"status\": \"not_found_in_k8s\"}`\n238: \n239: #### Scenario: _get_k8s_status\n240: \n241: - **GIVEN** a standard K8s deployment\n242: - **WHEN** `_get_k8s_status` runs\n243: - **THEN** it SHALL call `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status` and return the result\n244: \n245: ---\n246: \n247: ## Cross-cutting\n248: \n249: ### Requirement: Error handling for invoke/status\n250: \n251: Both commands SHALL use `_handle_error(e, command_name, verbose)` for subcommand exceptions.\n252: \n253: #### Scenario: verbose traceback\n254: \n255: - **GIVEN** a subcommand's local `--verbose` is `True` but global `-v` was not passed\n256: - **WHEN** an error occurs in that subcommand\n257: - **THEN** traceback SHALL still be printed because `_handle_error` receives the subcommand's `verbose` flag\n258: \n259: ### Requirement: Provider selection\n260: \n261: The `--provider` flag SHALL determine which backend is used for both invoke and status.\n262: \n263: #### Scenario: provider=agentcube\n264: \n265: - **GIVEN** `--provider agentcube`\n266: - **WHEN** invoke or status runs\n267: - **THEN** the system SHALL use `AgentCubeProvider` for K8s CR operations\n268: \n269: #### Scenario: provider=k8s\n270: \n271: - **GIVEN** `--provider k8s`\n272: - **WHEN** invoke or status runs\n273: - **THEN** the system SHALL use `KubernetesProvider` for standard K8s operations\n\n(End of file - total 273 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-023: CLI invoke/status ÕæĮõ╗ż ŌĆö Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `cmd/cli`\n- **Language:** Python\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/spec.md`, `cli-toolkit/design.md`\n\n## Scope\n\nThis delta spec covers the `invoke` and `status` CLI commands, their runtime classes (`InvokeRuntime`, `StatusRuntime`), and associated provider integrations (`AgentCubeProvider`, `KubernetesProvider`).\n\n---\n\n## invoke Command\n\n### Requirement: invoke command entry point\n\nThe system SHALL provide an `invoke` subcommand that POSTs JSON payload to the published agent endpoint, supporting both `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR) and `k8s` (Deployment/Service) providers.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775861462031,"end":1775861462039}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775861462119,"sessionID":"ses_28669b5caffeqYLfdG2bo5GERy","part":{"id":"prt_d79977457001mHiIotWR7pnd8g","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d79976919001otqXA851gaV2SY","sessionID":"ses_28669b5caffeqYLfdG2bo5GERy","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":38147,"input":38064,"output":72,"reasoning":11,"cache":{"write":0,"read":0}},"cost":0.010642697}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775861463903,"sessionID":"ses_28669b5caffeqYLfdG2bo5GERy","part":{"id":"prt_d79977b5b001TkB2mna2ZCDYBX","messageID":"msg_d7997747f001LfmW9oPn5m2YKv","sessionID":"ses_28669b5caffeqYLfdG2bo5GERy","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775861528972,"sessionID":"ses_28669b5caffeqYLfdG2bo5GERy","part":{"id":"prt_d7997864a001SyiUZSTqr04zfb","messageID":"msg_d7997747f001LfmW9oPn5m2YKv","sessionID":"ses_28669b5caffeqYLfdG2bo5GERy","type":"text","text":"Now I'll overwrite with the AR-026 delta spec:","time":{"start":1775861528971,"end":1775861528971}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861529013,"sessionID":"ses_28669b5caffeqYLfdG2bo5GERy","part":{"id":"prt_d7997879f001rqje6QdBUmtDHQ","messageID":"msg_d7997747f001LfmW9oPn5m2YKv","sessionID":"ses_28669b5caffeqYLfdG2bo5GERy","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_2cbaa5e4da904dbc907c0b35","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-026: K8s/AgentCube Provider ŌĆö Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `cmd/cli`\n- **Language:** Python\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/spec.md`, `cli-toolkit/design.md`, `deployment/client-go.md`\n\n## Scope\n\nThis delta spec covers `KubernetesProvider` and `AgentCubeProvider` classes ŌĆö their deployment, status retrieval, namespace management, name sanitization, CRD availability checks, and K8s client initialization error handling. Provider selection in CLI publish/status/invoke commands is also specified.\n\n---\n\n## KubernetesProvider\n\n### Requirement: KubernetesProvider constructor\nThe system SHALL initialize `KubernetesProvider` with namespace, verbose flag, and optional kubeconfig path.\n\n#### Scenario: default constructor\n- **GIVEN** `KubernetesProvider()` is called with no arguments\n- **WHEN** the instance is created\n- **THEN** `namespace` SHALL default to `\"default\"`, `verbose` to `False`, and `kubeconfig` to `None`\n\n#### Scenario: custom kubeconfig\n- **GIVEN** a custom kubeconfig path is provided\n- **WHEN** the instance is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL load the K8s configuration from that path\n\n#### Scenario: kubeconfig not found\n- **GIVEN** no kubeconfig file exists at the default or specified path\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider` is initialized\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise an exception indicating kubeconfig is missing\n\n#### Scenario: invalid kubeconfig\n- **GIVEN** a kubeconfig file exists but contains invalid YAML or cluster config\n- **WHEN** the provider is initialized\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise an exception with the parsing or connection error\n\n### Requirement: KubernetesProvider._ensure_namespace\nThe system SHALL create the target namespace if it does not already exist before deploying resources.\n\n#### Scenario: namespace already exists\n- **GIVEN** `KubernetesProvider` is initialized with `namespace=\"default\"`\n- **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL detect the namespace exists and take no action\n\n#### Scenario: namespace does not exist\n- **GIVEN** `KubernetesProvider` is initialized with `namespace=\"my-agents\"`\n- **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace` is called and the namespace is not found\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create the namespace via the K8s API and log the creation\n\n#### Scenario: namespace creation failure\n- **GIVEN** the user lacks RBAC permissions to create namespaces\n- **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace` is called for a non-existent namespace\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise an exception with the K8s API error surfaced to the caller\n\n### Requirement: KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent\nThe system SHALL deploy an agent as a standard K8s Deployment + NodePort Service.\n\n#### Scenario: full deploy flow\n- **GIVEN** valid `agent_name`, `image_url`, `port`\n- **WHEN** `deploy_agent` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Call `_ensure_namespace`\n  2. Call `_create_deployment`\n  3. Call `_create_service`\n  4. Call `wait_for_deployment_ready(..., timeout=120)`\n  5. Return result including `deployment_name`, `service_name`, `namespace`, `replicas`, `container_port`, `node_port`, `service_url` as `http://localhost:{node_port}`\n\n### Requirement: KubernetesProvider._create_deployment\nThe system SHALL create or patch a Kubernetes `Deployment` with the agent container spec.\n\n#### Scenario: create new deployment\n- **GIVEN** no existing deployment with the given name\n- **WHEN** `_create_deployment` is called with `name`, `image_url`, `port`, `replicas`, and optional `env_vars`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create a `Deployment` with:\n  - `metadata.name` = sanitized name\n  - `spec.replicas` = provided replicas (default 1)\n  - `spec.template.spec.containers[0].image` = `image_url`\n  - `spec.template.spec.containers[0].ports[0].containerPort` = `port`\n  - `spec.template.spec.containers[0].env` populated from `env_vars` if provided\n  - `spec.template.spec.containers[0].command` set from `entrypoint` if provided\n\n#### Scenario: patch existing deployment\n- **GIVEN** a deployment with the given name already exists\n- **WHEN** `_create_deployment` is called with updated `image_url` or `replicas`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL patch the existing deployment with the new spec\n\n### Requirement: KubernetesProvider._create_service\nThe system SHALL create or patch a `NodePort` `Service` to expose the deployment.\n\n#### Scenario: create NodePort service with auto-assigned port\n- **GIVEN** `node_port` is `None`\n- **WHEN** `_create_service` is called with `name` and `port`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create a `Service` of type `NodePort` with K8s auto-assigned node port in range 30000-32767\n\n#### Scenario: create NodePort service with explicit port\n- **GIVEN** `node_port` is provided (e.g., `30080`)\n- **WHEN** `_create_service` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create a `Service` with `spec.ports[0].nodePort` = the provided value\n\n#### Scenario: invalid NodePort range\n- **GIVEN** `node_port` is outside 30000-32767\n- **WHEN** `_create_service` is called\n- **THEN** the K8s API SHALL reject the request and the system SHALL surface the error\n\n### Requirement: KubernetesProvider.wait_for_deployment_ready\nThe system SHALL poll the deployment until all replicas are ready or timeout is exceeded.\n\n#### Scenario: deployment becomes ready\n- **GIVEN** a deployment is rolling out\n- **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready` is called and pods become ready within timeout\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return successfully\n\n#### Scenario: deployment timeout\n- **GIVEN** a deployment name\n- **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready` exceeds `timeout` seconds (default `120`)\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `TimeoutError`\n\n### Requirement: KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status\nThe system SHALL retrieve the current status of a deployed agent including pod health.\n\n#### Scenario: agent running with ready pods\n- **GIVEN** a deployment exists with all replicas ready\n- **WHEN** `get_agent_status` is called with `agent_name`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return a dict containing `status: \"running\"`, `replicas`, `ready_replicas`, and pod details\n\n#### Scenario: agent deployment not found\n- **GIVEN** no deployment exists with the given name\n- **WHEN** `get_agent_status` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return `{\"status\": \"not_found\"}` or raise an appropriate exception\n\n#### Scenario: agent in rollout progress\n- **GIVEN** a deployment exists but not all replicas are ready\n- **WHEN** `get_agent_status` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return status indicating rollout in progress with `ready_replicas < replicas`\n\n### Requirement: KubernetesProvider.delete_agent\nThe system SHALL delete a deployment and its service, ignoring 404s on individual deletes.\n\n#### Scenario: successful deletion\n- **GIVEN** `delete_agent` is called with an existing agent name\n- **WHEN** deletion completes\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `{\"status\": \"deleted\", \"deployment_name\", \"namespace\"}` ignoring 404 on individual deletes\n\n### Requirement: KubernetesProvider._sanitize_name\nThe system SHALL sanitize agent names to be valid Kubernetes resource names.\n\n#### Scenario: valid name unchanged\n- **GIVEN** a name containing only lowercase alphanumeric characters and hyphens\n- **WHEN** `_sanitize_name` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return the name unchanged\n\n#### Scenario: invalid characters replaced\n- **GIVEN** a name containing uppercase letters, underscores, or other invalid characters\n- **WHEN** `_sanitize_name` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return a name with invalid characters replaced (e.g., lowercased, underscores ŌåÆ hyphens)\n\n---\n\n## AgentCubeProvider\n\n### Requirement: AgentCubeProvider constructor\nThe system SHALL initialize `AgentCubeProvider` with namespace, verbose flag, and optional kubeconfig path.\n\n#### Scenario: default constructor\n- **GIVEN** `AgentCubeProvider()` is called with no arguments\n- **WHEN** the instance is created\n- **THEN** `namespace` SHALL default to `\"default\"`, `verbose` to `False`, and `kubeconfig` to `None`\n\n#### Scenario: cluster unreachable\n- **GIVEN** kubeconfig is valid but the cluster API server is unreachable\n- **WHEN** any provider method makes a K8s API call\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise a connection error surfaced via CLI `_handle_error`\n\n### Requirement: AgentCubeProvider._ensure_namespace\nThe system SHALL ensure the target namespace exists before creating AgentRuntime CRs.\n\n#### Scenario: namespace created for CR deployment\n- **GIVEN** `AgentCubeProvider` is initialized with a non-default namespace\n- **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace` is called and namespace does not exist\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create the namespace before proceeding with CR operations\n\n### Requirement: AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime\nThe system SHALL create or patch an `AgentRuntime` custom resource with full spec.\n\nCR API: `group=\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"`, `version=\"v1alpha1\"`, `plural=\"agentruntimes\"`.\n\n#### Scenario: create AgentRuntime CR with all fields\n- **GIVEN** valid metadata with `router_url`, `workload_manager_url`, readiness probe config\n- **WHEN** `deploy_agent_runtime` is called with `agent_name`, `image_url`, `port`, `entrypoint`, `env_vars`, and probe settings\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create an `AgentRuntime` CR with:\n  - `spec.image` = `image_url`\n  - `spec.port` = `port`\n  - `spec.entrypoint` = `entrypoint` if provided\n  - `spec.env` = merged from `env_vars` + `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` + `ROUTER_URL` (from params or environment)\n  - `spec.readinessProbe` with `httpGet.path` and `httpGet.port` from probe settings\n  - `spec.sessionTimeout` = `\"15m\"`\n  - `spec.maxSessionDuration` = `\"8h\"`\n  - `spec.imagePullSecrets` = `[{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]`\n\n#### Scenario: patch existing AgentRuntime CR\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` CR with the given name already exists\n- **WHEN** `deploy_agent_runtime` is called with updated fields\n- **THEN** the system SHALL patch the existing CR with the new spec\n\n#### Scenario: missing readiness probe fields\n- **GIVEN** metadata lacks `readiness_probe_path` or `readiness_probe_port`\n- **WHEN** `deploy_agent_runtime` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL either use defaults or omit the readiness probe from the CR spec\n\n#### Scenario: environment variable fallback\n- **GIVEN** `env_vars` does not contain `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` or `ROUTER_URL`\n- **WHEN** `deploy_agent_runtime` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL read `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` / `ROUTER_URL` from the process environment and inject them into the CR spec\n\n### Requirement: AgentCubeProvider._sanitize_name\nThe system SHALL sanitize names for AgentRuntime CR resource naming.\n\n#### Scenario: CR name sanitization\n- **GIVEN** an agent name with invalid K8s characters\n- **WHEN** `_sanitize_name` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return a DNS-1123 compliant name suitable for CR `metadata.name`\n\n### Requirement: AgentCubeProvider.get_agent_runtime\nThe system SHALL retrieve an existing AgentRuntime CR by name and namespace.\n\n#### Scenario: CR exists\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` CR exists with the given name in the namespace\n- **WHEN** `get_agent_runtime` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return the CR object as a dict\n\n#### Scenario: CR not found\n- **GIVEN** no `AgentRuntime` CR exists with the given name\n- **WHEN** `get_agent_runtime` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return `None`\n\n### Requirement: CRD availability check\nThe system SHALL verify that the AgentRuntime CRD is installed before attempting CR operations.\n\n#### Scenario: CRD not installed\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube` but the `agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` CRD is not registered\n- **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider` attempts to create or get a CR\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise an error indicating the CRD is not installed\n\n#### Scenario: CRD installed and accessible\n- **GIVEN** the CRD is registered and the user has RBAC permissions\n- **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider` performs CR operations\n- **THEN** the system SHALL succeed in creating/reading/updating AgentRuntime CRs\n\n---\n\n## Provider Selection in CLI Commands\n\n### Requirement: Publish provider routing\nThe system SHALL route publish operations to the correct provider based on `--provider`.\n\n#### Scenario: publish with --provider agentcube\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `publish --provider agentcube`\n- **WHEN** the publish command executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use `AgentCubeProvider` and call `deploy_agent_runtime`\n\n#### Scenario: publish with --provider k8s\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `publish --provider k8s`\n- **WHEN** the publish command executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use `KubernetesProvider` and call `deploy_agent` with `replicas` from options\n\n### Requirement: Status provider routing\nThe system SHALL route status operations to the correct provider based on `--provider`.\n\n#### Scenario: status with --provider agentcube\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `status --provider agentcube`\n- **WHEN** the status command executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use `StatusRuntime` with `provider=\"agentcube\"` and call `_get_cr_k8s_status`\n\n#### Scenario: status with --provider k8s\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `status --provider k8s`\n- **WHEN** the status command executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use `StatusRuntime` with `provider=\"k8s\"` and call `_get_k8s_status`\n\n### Requirement: Invoke provider routing\nThe system SHALL route invoke operations to the correct provider based on `--provider`.\n\n#### Scenario: invoke with --provider agentcube\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `invoke --provider agentcube`\n- **WHEN** the invoke command executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use `InvokeRuntime` with `provider=\"agentcube\"` and rewrite URL to AgentRuntime CR invocation path when `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`\n\n#### Scenario: invoke with --provider k8s\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `invoke --provider k8s`\n- **WHEN** the invoke command executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use `InvokeRuntime` with `provider=\"k8s\"` and invoke via standard deployment endpoint\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775861528964,"end":1775861529010}}}}
